    "ingredients_identification": {
        "ez_nlc_preparation_method": "The oily phase (stearic acid and oleic acid, 30%) was melted at 348°K. The aqueous phase (1% Tween 80 and 2% poloxamer 188 in distilled water) was heated to the same temperature. 10mg EZ was added to the molten lipid. The aqueous phase was added dropwise to the oily phase under magnetic stirring at 1400rpm and 333°K for 15min. The pre-emulsion was ultrasonicated using a probe sonicator at 100% amplitude for 5min. The dispersion was mixed with drying excipients (Avicel alone or with mannitol) (5-7.5 w/%) until a homogeneous paste was formed. The paste was frozen at 253°K overnight and lyophilized (pre-freezing at 193°K for 15min, ramp 20min, main drying at 3 mbar for 6h). The resulting powder was mixed with 10mg magnesium stearate, 10mg talc, and CCS.",
        "absorbance_wavelength_nm": 231
    },
